Description: Morality In Media The leading National Organization opposing pornography and indecency through public education and application of the law.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, Southern US
Full Description: Morality in Media, Inc. (MIM) was launched by an interfaith group of clergy in the Upper Eastside of Manhattan (NYC) in 1962 after grade school children were caught with hardcore pornography. Now national in scope, MIM works through constitutional means to curb traffic in obscenity and uphold standards of decency in media. Common sense, anecdotal evidence and social science research all point to a link between obscenity and indecency and harmful consequences. In 1968, one of the clergy, Fr. Morton A. Hill, was appointed by President Johnson to serve on the Presidential Commission on Obscenity and Pornography. In 1970, the Commission issued a report recommending that obscenity be legalized for consenting adults. Fr. Hill and another Commissioner issued a minority report describing the majority report as a “Magna Carta for the pornographer” and, in so doing, helped save obscenity laws. President Nixon and Congress also rejected the majority report, and the Supreme Court later cited the Hill-Link minority report in upholding obscenity laws.

Leading the EV charging industry, dedicated to widespread adoption by building essential EV infrastructure.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Evfleetchargers is a leading force in charging solutions, specializing in building and operating the infrastructure essential for expediting the widespread adoption of electric vehicles (EVs). As a prominent public fast charging provider, Evfleetchargers boasts a network of over 5,000 fast charging locations across more than three countries, including stations deployed through its white-label service offering. Since its establishment in 2021, the company has been at the forefront of the electric mobility movement, providing cutting-edge services for individual drivers, commercial fleets, and businesses. Key Highlights: - Fast Charging Network: Evfleetchargers operates one of the nation's largest public fast charging networks, with over 5,000 locations strategically positioned across multiple countries. - White Label Service: The company's white label service offering ensures a seamless and branded charging experience for partners, including automakers, fleet operators, and retail hosts. - Partnerships for Accelerated Electrification: Evfleetchargers is actively driving transportation electrification through strategic partnerships with automakers, fleet operators, retail hosts such as grocery stores, shopping centers, and gas stations, as well as engagement with policy leaders and other organizations. - Innovative Software Products: With a rapidly expanding network, Evfleetchargers provides robust software products and unique service offerings for both drivers and partners. Notable features include Evfleetchargers Inside and Evfleetchargers Rewards, contributing to a world-class charging experience. - Investment Opportunities: Evfleetchargers empowers individuals and businesses by offering investment opportunities in the electric vehicle charging sector. Investors can earn daily returns by owning or co-owning EV chargers, contributing to the growth of sustainable transportation. Mission and Vision: Mission: To build, manage, and operate EV charging infrastructure, empowering individuals and businesses to own or co-own EV chargers. Vision: To enable 10 million individuals to own their EV chargers, generating passive income and contributing to a transition from fossil fuels to renewable energy. Achievements: - Recorded more than 29 million charging sessions. - Hosts more than 5,000 EV chargers in its charging network. Problem Solution and Competitive Advantage: Evfleetchargers addresses the challenge of EV charging ownership by empowering individuals and businesses to own or co-own chargers, providing a unique opportunity for passive income. The company's competitive advantage lies in its commitment to offering investment opportunities, a clear distinction from other companies solely focused on charging profits from EV car users. Evfleetchargers manages the chargers on behalf of owners, remitting profits regularly, and facilitates co-ownership to accommodate various financial capacities, ultimately contributing to a sustainable and accessible electric mobility future.

Description: Cerent Corporation was an optical equipment maker based in Petaluma, California. It was founded in 1997 as Fiberlane Communications with
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Cerent Corporation was an optical equipment maker based in Petaluma, California. It was founded in 1997 as Fiberlane Communications with three divisions: Systems in Petaluma, Chip Design in Redwood City, California and Network Management Systems in Burnaby, British Columbia. In early 1998 the company split into two companies with the Petaluma branch becoming Cerent and the Burnaby and Redwood City branches becoming Siara Networks. Cerent's first product was the Cerent 454. In August 1999, the company was sold to Cisco Systems for $7.2 billion and became the foundation of Cisco's Optical Transport Business Unit. The Cerent 454 was rebranded the Cisco 15454 and became the fastest product (at that time) to hit the $1B annual sales rate by selling $250 million in its second quarter as a Cisco business unit. In November 1999 Redback bought Siara Systems for $4.3 billion.

Headquarters Regions: Greater San Diego Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Maxim Athletic, together with its subsidiaries, designs, develops, manufactures, markets and sells athletic uniforms and apparel while providing inspiration and know-how to aspiring athletes and those with athletic ambitions.  The company offers team uniforms in twelve categories; football, baseball, softball, basketball, lacrosse, soccer, volleyball, track and field, cross country, tennis, golf and hockey.  The company also offers training apparel and outerwear for men, women and children.  The company currently sells its products wholesale to Team Sporting Good Dealers who market and sell to youth leagues, travel teams, high schools, colleges and semi- professional teams.  Team Sporting Good Dealers market and sell online, in their stores and through travelling sales reps.  The company has sales throughout the United States and Europe.  The company owns and manages its own factory in Tijuana, Mexico.  Company owned, cross-border manufacturing provides a unique competitive advantage. Maxim Athletic is able to provide faster, more reliable delivery than its competitors.  In a survey of 2,400 high school coaches, eighty five percent (85%) complained of poor service, directly related to late deliveries and long delivery times.   Each coach responded by saying they would be very open to a new supplier who could provide more reliable delivery and service. Management believes there’s a $100,000,000 opportunity for the company in Team Sporting Goods. While the company is currently focused on the Team Sporting Goods niche market, it plans to leverage its position in team sporting goods to launch a retail division.  Management believes there is a billion dollar opportunity in consumer retail sales.  Maxim Athletic competitors spend billions of dollars acquiring professional leagues, high profile athletes and entertainers to create an elite image.  Maxim Athletic will use a proprietary process to compete with industry giants at a fraction of the cost.

Description: Find exactly the equation you're looking for, every time.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: EQNS is a New York City based company that strives to advance education in the sciences by providing the academic community with the ability to quickly navigate through a large expanse of equations to easily find the correct equation, at the proper level. EQNS is designed to attempt to answer the age old question: "which equation is it again?" Education in the sciences is just as reliant on equations as it is concept driven. Formal proofs and mathematical representations are often essential to fully convince individuals of otherwise ungrounded conceptual claims.  At EQNS, we are striving to eliminate the hunt for and memorization of equations. We believe that it's hard enough to solve the equations and to correctly implement the formulas; there is no need to make them impossible to find as well. With this in mind, we have developed a website which is extremely easy to navigate. We let you, the user, narrow in on your equation by field, level, and branch. Additionally, we provide unrivaled clarity and conciseness. With links to practice problems and citations to papers, you can always rest assured that the listed equations are accurate and that you will know how they are implemented.

Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, Inland Empire, West Coast
Full Description: PlantCML, an EADS North America company, is the leading provider of mission critical communications and response technologies for public safety, business continuity and homeland defense. Their clients range from first responder operations to global corporations to military deployments.   Today, they are pioneering next-generation solutions through IP-enabled call processing applications, interoperable P25-based radio systems and highly advanced emergency notification technology. Their products and services are resident in 14 of the top 20 most populous U.S. cities, and internationally in 15 countries.
